oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Unidentified metal box
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Hinged rectangular box of brass and iron. Outside battering gives it the appearance of being handmade. Interior floor contains three circular bases that could be candlestick holders. Onsite historian believed the box to be trench art, possibly of the World War I era.
oai_dc:dc.dc:source: Tennessee State Library and Archives, Nashville, Davidson County, Tennessee
